org.schwering.evi.core
Class ModuleContainer

java.lang.Object
  org.schwering.evi.core.ModuleContainer
public final class ModuleContainer
extends java.lang.Object

Provides access to and control over a module.
This class administers the module's main class, its id, its version number, the module's requirements and, more importantly, also all current instances of the module.

ModuleContainer and ModuleLoader set up the core classes of the module engine.
The most interesting methods for module developers are the following:

  • ModuleLoader.getLoadedModule(String)
  • ModuleFactory.newInstance(ModuleContainer)
  • ModuleFactory.disposeInstance(IModule)
  • getInstances()
  • addListener(IModuleListener)

getPriority

public int getPriority()
Returns the module's priority in the module hierarchy. The first loaded module has the priority 0, the second 1 etc.

Note that if a module has been loaded and unloaded again, its priority is not given to any module again. An example: Let module X have the priority 2. If module X is unloaded, no other module will get the priority 2. Instead, it will go on with 3 etc.

Returns:
The module's position at the loading chain.
